		<description><![CDATA[<p>A recent <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/13/opinion/if-it-feels-right.html?_r=3&#38;emc=eta1&#38;src=ISMR_HP_LI_LST_FB&#38;pagewanted=all" target="_blank">op-ed</a> by David Brooks brought my attention to a study conducted by Notre Dame sociologist Christian Smith and some of his colleagues &#8212; the results of which have been published in a book entitled <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Lost-Transition-Emerging-Adulthood-ebook/dp/B005FVPEW8/ref=reg_hu-rd_add_1_dp" target="_blank">Lost in Transition</a> &#8211; that found that young adults are bad at &#8220;thinking and talking about [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style=""><div id='rdbWrapper'></div><script type='text/javascript'>
