		<description><![CDATA[<p>A couple of days ago, at <a href="http://theamericanscene.com/2011/08/09/the-cause-of-all-the-trouble">The American Scene</a>, Wheaton professor Alan Jacobs took Andrew Sullivan to task on his recent <a href="http://andrewsullivan.thedailybeast.com/2011/08/was-mlk-a-christianist.html">remarks</a>  about &#8220;Christianists,&#8221; a term he often uses to describe the Christian right, but which, more generally applied, refers to people who fuse &#8220;politics and religion for the advancement of political goals.&#8221; [...]]]></description>
